        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-476",
        "content": "The drive in the brake to the station, the ride to London in creased, but comfortable clothing, free as the air, at liberty to go to bed and rise when he liked, to choose his own dinner, to answer no call save the call of his conscience, to see-he checked himself.",
